      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I would advise against consuming wine with diazepam, as it can increase the sedative effects of the medication, leading to enhanced respiratory depression, drowsiness, and impairment of cognitive function. The recommended dosage of diazepam is typically taken with water only, as you've already been prescribed. Light use means taking the exact dose prescribed and not exceeding it, and adding wine might not be worth the risk of serious adverse effects. It's best to follow your doctor's guidance and recommendations strictly.",
